@McHobotheBobo I might have stated things in a slightly misleading way. There definitely is SOME worker representation in China, but the unions act more as mediators rather than advocates. Much like US trade unions they facilitate some minimum level of representation, but ultimately stifle any more radical tactics.

I find your description of the fall of communist Poland very strange. The collapse of Poland was caused by a failing economy and labor unrest that predates solidarity. The idea that Poland wouldn't of collapsed anyway if they had suppressed independent workers movements seems laughable to me. The fact that you think the party should suppress what was the will of the vast majority of workers is concerning.

MLs in one breath will denounce the AFL-ICO, and then in the next advocate entryism.
